:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"serp snippet tool\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=177313\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:421:\"<p>Would you like to learn how to use a SERP snippet tool to boost your clickthrough rates? A SERP snippet tool can help you make changes that deliver more traffic to your site. And it only takes a few minutes.&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-serp-snippet-tool/\">How to Use a SERP Snippet Tool to Improve Your Click-Through Rates</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Sherrie Gossett\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52564:\"<p>Would you like to learn how to use a SERP snippet tool to boost your clickthrough rates?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A SERP snippet tool can help you make changes that deliver more traffic to your site. And it only takes a few minutes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this tutorial, you&#8217;ll learn the easy way to use a SERP snippet tool to optimize your web pages for search engine results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What you&#8217;ll need</strong>: The <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO) Plugin</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-whats-a-serp-snippet-tool\">What&#8217;s a SERP Snippet Tool?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-1-download-the-all-in-one-seo-aioseo-plugin\">Step 1: Download and Install the All in One SEO (AIOSEO) Plugin</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-2-preview-your-web-page-as-a-google-search-snippet\">Step 2: Preview Your Web Page as a Google Search Snippet</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-3-set-your-post-title-title-tag\">Step 3: Set Your Post Title</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-4-optimize-your-meta-description\">Step 4: Optimize Your Description</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-5-optimize-your-slug\">Step 5: Optimize Your Slug</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-cheatsheet-search-snippet-guidelines\">Cheatsheet: Search Snippet Guidelines</a><ul></ul></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-whats-a-serp-snippet-tool\">What&#8217;s a SERP Snippet Tool?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A SERP snippet tool provides a preview of what a web page may look like in search results. (SERP stands for “search engine results page.”) <br><br>The preview includes the <strong>title</strong>, the <strong>URL</strong>, and a short <strong>description</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"297\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-serp-snippet-tool-example-1024x297.png\" alt=\"serp snippet preview\" class=\"wp-image-177329\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-serp-snippet-tool-example-1024x297.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-serp-snippet-tool-example-300x87.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-serp-snippet-tool-example-768x223.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-serp-snippet-tool-example-600x174.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-serp-snippet-tool-example-190x55.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-serp-snippet-tool-example-310x90.png 310w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/1-serp-snippet-tool-example.png 1059w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can use a SERP snippet tool to optimize these items so you can get higher click-through rates (CTRs).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s an easy way to do this.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-step-1-download-the-all-in-one-seo-aioseo-plugin\">Step 1: Download and Install the All in One SEO (AIOSEO) Plugin</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>First, we recommend that you <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">download the AIOSEO plugin</a>. This plugin includes a SERP snippet tool that gives you a preview of your page right in the WordPress editor.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO has thousands of 5-star reviews on WordPress.org and over 3 million people are using it. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It makes basic SEO tasks as simple as clicking a button or filling out a form field.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"485\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-1024x485.png\" alt=\"aioseo homepage\" class=\"wp-image-140989\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-1024x485.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-768x364.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-600x284.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-127x60.png 127w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-190x90.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage.png 1260w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"\">downloading AIOSEO</a>, log in to your WordPress editor. <br><br>Go to <strong>Plugins » Add New</strong> to install and activate AIOSEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Questions? Follow the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"\">instructions here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-step-2-preview-your-web-page-as-a-google-search-snippet\">Step 2: Preview Your Web Page as a Google Search Snippet</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, in your WordPress editor, navigate to any post that you want a <strong>preview </strong>of.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can access your Google search snippet in 2 ways:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>In WordPress’s <strong>Preview</strong> mode</li>\n\n\n\n<li>In WordPress’s <strong>Editing</strong> mode</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>In our tutorial example, we&#8217;ll be using a made-up post called &#8220;How to Create a Digital Strategy Today (Free Downloadable Template).”</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-option-1-start-in-wordpress-preview-mode\">Option 1: Start in WordPress Preview mode</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Click the <strong>preview button</strong> in WordPress to enter preview mode.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"322\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2-preview-wordpress-page-1024x322.png\" alt=\"wordpress preview\" class=\"wp-image-177330\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2-preview-wordpress-page-1024x322.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2-preview-wordpress-page-300x94.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2-preview-wordpress-page-768x241.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2-preview-wordpress-page-600x189.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2-preview-wordpress-page-190x60.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2-preview-wordpress-page-286x90.png 286w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2-preview-wordpress-page.png 1377w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Hover your cursor over the AIOSEO icon in the admin bar. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll see the <strong>SEO Preview</strong> option in the drop-down menu. Click it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1022\" height=\"244\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/3-aioseo-seo-preview.png\" alt=\"serp snippet tool\" class=\"wp-image-177331\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/3-aioseo-seo-preview.png 1022w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/3-aioseo-seo-preview-300x72.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/3-aioseo-seo-preview-768x183.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/3-aioseo-seo-preview-600x143.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/3-aioseo-seo-preview-190x45.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/3-aioseo-seo-preview-377x90.png 377w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now you can see your search snippet preview:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"574\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/4-SEO-preview-window-1024x574.png\" alt=\"serp snippet preview\" class=\"wp-image-177332\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/4-SEO-preview-window-1024x574.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/4-SEO-preview-window-300x168.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/4-SEO-preview-window-768x431.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/4-SEO-preview-window-704x396.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/4-SEO-preview-window-600x336.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/4-SEO-preview-window-107x60.png 107w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/4-SEO-preview-window-160x90.png 160w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/4-SEO-preview-window.png 1118w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Clicking the <strong>Edit Snippet</strong> button will allow you to change the title and meta-description. (This is covered in <strong>Step 3</strong> below.)</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-option-2-start-in-wordpress-editing-mode\">Option 2: Start in WordPress Editing mode</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In the WordPress editor, open a post.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>At the upper far right,</p>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>Click on the <strong>AIOSEO button</strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Then click <strong>General.</strong></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"725\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/5-aioseo-find-google-snippet-preview-1024x725.png\" alt=\"aioseo general settings\" class=\"wp-image-177334\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/5-aioseo-find-google-snippet-preview-1024x725.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/5-aioseo-find-google-snippet-preview-300x212.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/5-aioseo-find-google-snippet-preview-768x544.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/5-aioseo-find-google-snippet-preview-600x425.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/5-aioseo-find-google-snippet-preview-85x60.png 85w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/5-aioseo-find-google-snippet-preview-127x90.png 127w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/5-aioseo-find-google-snippet-preview.png 1040w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now you can see a preview of what your article may look like in Google&#8217;s search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"601\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/aioseo-serp-snippet-preview-highlighted-1024x601.png\" alt=\"serp snippet preview\" class=\"wp-image-177434\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/aioseo-serp-snippet-preview-highlighted-1024x601.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/aioseo-serp-snippet-preview-highlighted-300x176.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/aioseo-serp-snippet-preview-highlighted-768x450.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/aioseo-serp-snippet-preview-highlighted-600x352.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/aioseo-serp-snippet-preview-highlighted-102x60.png 102w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/aioseo-serp-snippet-preview-highlighted-153x90.png 153w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/aioseo-serp-snippet-preview-highlighted.png 1076w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-optional-toggle-between-desktop-and-mobile-views\">Optional: Toggle Between Desktop and Mobile Views</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Click the<strong> Edit Snippet</strong> button to see a wide-format preview (similar to what a desktop user would see).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/6-edit-google-snippet-preview-1024x646.jpg\" alt=\"aioseo edit serp snippet preview\" class=\"wp-image-177333\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/6-edit-google-snippet-preview-1024x646.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/6-edit-google-snippet-preview-300x189.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/6-edit-google-snippet-preview-768x485.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/6-edit-google-snippet-preview-600x379.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/6-edit-google-snippet-preview-95x60.jpg 95w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/6-edit-google-snippet-preview-143x90.jpg 143w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/6-edit-google-snippet-preview.jpg 1090w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now you’ll see a pop-up window that displays your SERP snippet in a wide format.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"487\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/7-desktop-google-snippet-preview-1024x487.png\" alt=\"aioseo serp snippet tool preview\" class=\"wp-image-177335\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/7-desktop-google-snippet-preview-1024x487.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/7-desktop-google-snippet-preview-300x143.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/7-desktop-google-snippet-preview-768x365.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/7-desktop-google-snippet-preview-600x285.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/7-desktop-google-snippet-preview-126x60.png 126w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/7-desktop-google-snippet-preview-189x90.png 189w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/7-desktop-google-snippet-preview.png 1117w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can toggle between <strong>desktop</strong> and <strong>mobile</strong> views by clicking the device icons at upper right.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"477\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/8-toggle-google-snippet-preview-1024x477.png\" alt=\"aioseo snippet preview options\" class=\"wp-image-177336\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/8-toggle-google-snippet-preview-1024x477.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/8-toggle-google-snippet-preview-300x140.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/8-toggle-google-snippet-preview-768x358.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/8-toggle-google-snippet-preview-600x280.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/8-toggle-google-snippet-preview-129x60.png 129w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/8-toggle-google-snippet-preview-193x90.png 193w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/8-toggle-google-snippet-preview.png 1105w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Keep this preview window open; we&#8217;ll be using it for the rest of the tutorial.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-step-3-set-your-post-title-title-tag\">Step 3: Set Your Post Title (Title Tag)</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let’s find out how to edit a post title for SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>If you’re viewing your post in <em>preview mode</em>, click<strong> Edit Snippet</strong>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>If you’re in <em>editing mode</em>, look underneath the Snippet Preview section: there&#8217;s a <strong>Post Title</strong> section.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>This Post Title section is where we’ll adjust our headline.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"305\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9-aioseo-post-title-field-2-1024x305.png\" alt=\"aioseo edit post title\" class=\"wp-image-177337\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9-aioseo-post-title-field-2-1024x305.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9-aioseo-post-title-field-2-300x89.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9-aioseo-post-title-field-2-768x229.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9-aioseo-post-title-field-2-600x179.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9-aioseo-post-title-field-2-190x57.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9-aioseo-post-title-field-2-302x90.png 302w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9-aioseo-post-title-field-2.png 1100w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>By default, AIOSEO populates the Post Title field with these 3 tags:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Post Title</strong> (this is the title of your article)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Separator </strong>(in this case, a dash)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Site Title</strong> (the name of your website).</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>These 3 items cause your<strong> title</strong> to be displayed this way in the search preview:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"269\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/10-aioseo-post-title-field-elements-1024x269.png\" alt=\"parts of a standard search snippet\" class=\"wp-image-177338\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/10-aioseo-post-title-field-elements-1024x269.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/10-aioseo-post-title-field-elements-300x79.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/10-aioseo-post-title-field-elements-768x202.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/10-aioseo-post-title-field-elements-600x157.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/10-aioseo-post-title-field-elements-190x50.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/10-aioseo-post-title-field-elements-343x90.png 343w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/10-aioseo-post-title-field-elements.png 1231w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-check-the-length-of-your-post-title\">Check the Length of your Post Title</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>SEO professionals often recommend keeping your article title under 60 or so characters.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is because longer titles may get cut off in search results. Here&#8217;s an example of that. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"233\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/11-serp-title-truncated-1024x233.png\" alt=\"truncated title in serp\" class=\"wp-image-177440\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/11-serp-title-truncated-1024x233.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/11-serp-title-truncated-300x68.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/11-serp-title-truncated-768x174.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/11-serp-title-truncated-600x136.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/11-serp-title-truncated-190x43.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/11-serp-title-truncated-396x90.png 396w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/11-serp-title-truncated.png 1206w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>(Notice that Google places ellipses where words were cut off.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The AIOSEO preview recommends <strong>60 characters max</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In our tutorial example, we&#8217;re over the “max recommended characters.”</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"641\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/12-title-over-recommended-character-limit-1024x641.png\" alt=\"aioseo serp snippet tool character limit display\" class=\"wp-image-177441\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/12-title-over-recommended-character-limit-1024x641.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/12-title-over-recommended-character-limit-300x188.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/12-title-over-recommended-character-limit-768x480.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/12-title-over-recommended-character-limit-600x375.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/12-title-over-recommended-character-limit-96x60.png 96w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/12-title-over-recommended-character-limit-144x90.png 144w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/12-title-over-recommended-character-limit.png 1111w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s imagine that we don&#8217;t care about our site title or a separator displaying next to our article title in search results. (We actually don&#8217;t use these on our own site.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So we&#8217;ll delete the <strong>Site Title</strong> and <strong>Separator</strong> tags.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now the title is <strong>67 characters long</strong>. We&#8217;re still over the recommended length.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"973\" height=\"622\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/8a-title-length-over-recommended-67.png\" alt=\"aioseo serp snippet tool title character limit \" class=\"wp-image-177461\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/8a-title-length-over-recommended-67.png 973w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/8a-title-length-over-recommended-67-300x192.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/8a-title-length-over-recommended-67-768x491.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/8a-title-length-over-recommended-67-600x384.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/8a-title-length-over-recommended-67-94x60.png 94w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/8a-title-length-over-recommended-67-141x90.png 141w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So let&#8217;s delete the word &#8220;Downloadable&#8221; from the title. (You&#8217;ll need to scroll to the top of your post to delete words.)</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"929\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/13-title-within-character-limits-1.png\" alt=\"aioseo serp snippet tool title character limit\" class=\"wp-image-177462\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/13-title-within-character-limits-1.png 929w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/13-title-within-character-limits-1-300x155.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/13-title-within-character-limits-1-768x397.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/13-title-within-character-limits-1-600x310.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/13-title-within-character-limits-1-116x60.png 116w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/13-title-within-character-limits-1-174x90.png 174w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now our title is well within the recommended character limit.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-additional-tips\">Additional Tips</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-you-can-manually-type-in-your-title\">You Can Manually Type in Your Title</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>If you like, you can remove all the tags in the Post Title field, and manually type in the title you want to display in search results (The title you type in can <em>differ</em> from the title you placed at the top of your post.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also remove your manually typed title and put the tags back in by clicking on the buttons located above the Post Title field.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"495\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/14-add-title-tags-back-in-1024x495.png\" alt=\"aioseo serp snippet tool tags\" class=\"wp-image-177463\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/14-add-title-tags-back-in-1024x495.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/14-add-title-tags-back-in-300x145.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/14-add-title-tags-back-in-768x372.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/14-add-title-tags-back-in-600x290.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/14-add-title-tags-back-in-124x60.png 124w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/14-add-title-tags-back-in-186x90.png 186w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/14-add-title-tags-back-in.png 1079w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ll also notice that there&#8217;s an option to add <strong>emojis</strong> to your title. (Yes, these can show up in search results.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Depending on your brand voice, these may (or may not) be a good fit for you.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the example below, we&#8217;ve added 2 rocket emojis to our headline to make it stand out in search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"505\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/15-add-emoji-to-title-1-1024x505.png\" alt=\"aioseo serp snippet title within recommended character limit\" class=\"wp-image-177465\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/15-add-emoji-to-title-1-1024x505.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/15-add-emoji-to-title-1-300x148.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/15-add-emoji-to-title-1-768x379.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/15-add-emoji-to-title-1-600x296.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/15-add-emoji-to-title-1-122x60.png 122w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/15-add-emoji-to-title-1-183x90.png 183w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/15-add-emoji-to-title-1.png 1069w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can learn more about adding emojis to your title and description fields <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-emojis-to-your-wordpress-blog/\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-why-you-might-want-a-long-title\">Why You Might Want a Long Title</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Professional marketers often go over the “recommended character” limit. Here’s why.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As long as the words that appear within the 60-character limit form a clear and enticing title, you can include some <strong>additional keywords</strong> and information after that limit.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s an example from a recent blog post of ours:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/16-trun-1-1024x200.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-177469\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/16-trun-1-1024x200.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/16-trun-1-300x59.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/16-trun-1-768x150.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/16-trun-1-600x117.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/16-trun-1-190x37.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/16-trun-1-460x90.png 460w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/16-trun-1.png 1109w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The full title is: <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo-and-get-more-traffic/\">How to Use a WordPress FAQ Block to Boost SEO and Get <em>More Traffic</em></a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We added a keyword at the end (“Traffic”) which tells Google something about the content. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a result, if someone searches for “faq block traffic” our result may appear:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"422\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/17-faq-block-traffic-serp-1-1024x422.png\" alt=\"long title example in serp\" class=\"wp-image-177470\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/17-faq-block-traffic-serp-1-1024x422.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/17-faq-block-traffic-serp-1-300x124.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/17-faq-block-traffic-serp-1-768x316.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/17-faq-block-traffic-serp-1-600x247.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/17-faq-block-traffic-serp-1-146x60.png 146w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/17-faq-block-traffic-serp-1-219x90.png 219w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/17-faq-block-traffic-serp-1.png 1234w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Lastly, if your article lands a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/optimize-content-for-featured-snippets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">featured snippet</a> spot, there’s more room for the title. In the example below, the full title displays at the top.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"960\" height=\"512\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/18-featured-snippet-long-title-example-1.png\" alt=\"featured snippet example\" class=\"wp-image-177471\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/18-featured-snippet-long-title-example-1.png 960w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/18-featured-snippet-long-title-example-1-300x160.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/18-featured-snippet-long-title-example-1-768x410.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/18-featured-snippet-long-title-example-1-600x320.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/18-featured-snippet-long-title-example-1-113x60.png 113w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/18-featured-snippet-long-title-example-1-169x90.png 169w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The takeaway</strong>: “Recommended” is a guideline that helps you understand <em>what words may get cut off in your title. </em>Once you know this, you can decide whether you want to create a longer title. Google has <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I5skhmp6Cxg&amp;t=5109s\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">confirmed</a> there can be SEO value in doing so and they’ve said you shouldn’t focus too much on the length. But avoid excessively long titles  filled with “<a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/white-hat-vs-black-hat-seo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">keyword stuffing</a>.” That can get your site penalized.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-meta-title-tag-vs-seo-title-whats-the-difference\">Meta Title Tag vs. SEO Title: What’s the Difference?</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>When you read articles about optimizing your title, you’ll often see these related words used:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Meta title tag</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SEO Title</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The title that you set to be displayed in search results will be wrapped with an HTML tag called a title tag. </p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;title&gt;Here’s My Article Title&lt;/title&gt;</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>As we discussed, you can set a different title for search engines than the one on your page. The one you choose for search engines is sometimes called the <strong>SEO title</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-theme-notice-box\" role=\"alert\">\n<p>Google (or other search engines) do not guarantee that they will display your preferred title. Write a clear, descriptive title to increase the chances that yours will display. Google may display a different title if it matches a particular search query better.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-step-4-optimize-your-meta-description\">Step 4: Optimize Your Meta Description</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Just like your title, your article description (called a &#8220;meta description&#8221;) has a recommended maximum length: <strong>160 characters</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In All in One SEO, the <strong>Meta Description</strong> field is directly below the <strong>Post Title</strong> field.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ll want to manually type in a meta description that describes your article in clear terms.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So the first thing we&#8217;ll do is remove the default <strong>Excerpt</strong> tag.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"289\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/19-aioseo-meta-description-field-1-1024x289.png\" alt=\"aioseo meta description field\" class=\"wp-image-177474\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/19-aioseo-meta-description-field-1-1024x289.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/19-aioseo-meta-description-field-1-300x85.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/19-aioseo-meta-description-field-1-768x217.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/19-aioseo-meta-description-field-1-600x169.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/19-aioseo-meta-description-field-1-190x54.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/19-aioseo-meta-description-field-1-319x90.png 319w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/19-aioseo-meta-description-field-1.png 1088w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This Excerpt tag tells Google to pull any excerpt from your page. Often, when there&#8217;s no meta description specified, Google will pull some text from the beginning of your article. And it will usually be cut off and followed by ellipses.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s what we see happening in the snippet preview here:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"310\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/20-metadescription-preview-1-1024x310.png\" alt=\"aioseo serp snippet preview\" class=\"wp-image-177475\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/20-metadescription-preview-1-1024x310.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/20-metadescription-preview-1-300x91.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/20-metadescription-preview-1-768x232.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/20-metadescription-preview-1-600x181.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/20-metadescription-preview-1-190x57.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/20-metadescription-preview-1-298x90.png 298w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/20-metadescription-preview-1.png 1247w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let&#8217;s type in a meta description. We want to encourage searchers to click on our article, so we&#8217;ll try to provide them with a good reason to do so.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"269\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/21-meta-description-example-1024x269.png\" alt=\"meta description example\" class=\"wp-image-177476\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/21-meta-description-example-1024x269.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/21-meta-description-example-300x79.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/21-meta-description-example-768x202.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/21-meta-description-example-600x158.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/21-meta-description-example-190x50.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/21-meta-description-example-342x90.png 342w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/21-meta-description-example.png 1235w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Our new meta description is within the recommended length. It&#8217;s concise and describes what our article offers.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-whats-a-meta-description-tag\">What&#8217;s a Meta Description Tag?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A meta description <em>tag</em> is HTML code that tells Google (and other search engines) &#8220;This is the description the publisher would like displayed in search engine results.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you type in your meta description, AIOSEO saves it and applies this HTML code to it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is what a meta description looks like in HTML.</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;meta name=\"description\" content=\"Use our easy 3-step template to create a digital strategy that grows traffic, conversions, and revenue. &#91;Bonus: Get it reviewed by our pros within 24 hrs.]\" /&gt;</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>What&#8217;s next? Let&#8217;s take a look at your <strong>slug</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-step-5-optimize-your-slug\">Step 5: Optimize Your Slug</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>What&#8217;s a slug? (No, it&#8217;s not that thing eating your petunias. We&#8217;re pretty sure you wouldn&#8217;t want to optimize <em>that</em>.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A &#8220;slug&#8221; is the last part of a page URL. It&#8217;s preceded by a forward slash (&#8220;/&#8221;) and provides a unique &#8220;address&#8221; for your web page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the example below,<strong> /welcome-to-my-website</strong> is the slug.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>mysite.com/blog/<strong>welcome-to-my-new-website</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Many content management systems, including WordPress, automatically generate a slug that matches your page title word-for-word.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So now that you know what a slug is, how do you optimize it for SEO?</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-include-your-focus-keyword\">Include Your Focus Keyword</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Slugs are a <a href=\"https://www.searchenginejournal.com/ranking-factors/urls/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">minor ranking factor</a>. Google’s John Mueller has called them a “very lightweight factor” that’s primarily used as a signal for classifying content when Google first encounters a page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Since WordPress turns your post title into a slug, as long as you <em>include your keyword in your title</em> you should be fine.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Imagine our focus keyword is &#8220;<strong>fix drywall holes</strong>.&#8221; Here are some examples of slugs that include the keyword:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>/<strong>fix-drywall-holes</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>/how-to-<strong>fix-drywall-holes</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>/how-to-<strong>fix-drywall-holes</strong>-easily</p>\n\n\n\n<p>/best-way-to-<strong>fix-drywall-holes</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-how-to-change-your-slug-in-wordpress\">How to Change Your Slug in WordPress</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If for any reason you want to change your slug, you can do so easily.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the WordPress editor, click the <strong>Settings</strong> gear icon at the upper right.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then go to <strong>Post » Permalink</strong>. You&#8217;ll see a field where you can edit the slug.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"946\" height=\"364\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/23-wordpress-url-slug-field.png\" alt=\"wordpress edit url slug\" class=\"wp-image-177480\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/23-wordpress-url-slug-field.png 946w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/23-wordpress-url-slug-field-300x115.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/23-wordpress-url-slug-field-768x296.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/23-wordpress-url-slug-field-600x231.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/23-wordpress-url-slug-field-156x60.png 156w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/23-wordpress-url-slug-field-234x90.png 234w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Great, now you know how to check and optimize your:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Post title</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Meta description</li>\n\n\n\n<li>and slug.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s a handy cheat sheet covering what you learned.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-cheatsheet-search-snippet-guidelines\">Cheatsheet: Search Snippet Guidelines</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>SEO item</strong></td><td><strong>Approximate character limit before cut-off</strong></td><td><strong>Tips</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Post or Page Title</td><td>60</td><td>Include your focus keyword. <br>Title should inform and persuade.<br>Make sure your title makes sense before the cut-off point.</td></tr><tr><td>Meta description</td><td>160</td><td>Include your focus keyword and one or more related keywords. <br>Include what makes your article unique or valuable.</td></tr><tr><td>Slug</td><td>Not applicable</td><td>Include your focus keyword</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-aioseo-global-search-snippet-settings\">AIOSEO: Global Search Snippet Tool Settings</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In AIOSEO, you can set your own default preferences for how all your search snippets display in the preview.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is easy to do, so there’s no need to rely on a webmaster.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the <strong>admin bar</strong> of your WordPress editor go to:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>AIOSEO Settings » Search Appearance » Content types</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can set your preferences for each content type on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, if you don&#8217;t want the Site Title (or a Separator) to display on any of your WordPress <strong><em>posts</em></strong>, then remove those gray tags.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also create different settings for your WordPress <strong><em>pages</em></strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>(By default, WordPress sites have 2 web page types:<strong> Page</strong> and <strong>Post</strong>. Post refers to articles, announcements, or blog posts. Pages are typically landing pages that form your main navigation points.)</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-pro-tips-and-extras\">Pro Tips and Extras</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are a few additional tips and tricks to help you understand and craft a good SERP snippet.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-start-with-a-focus-keyword\">Start with a focus keyword</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Before you write an article you should choose a main topic. In SEO this is called a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/using-the-focus-keyphrase-to-analyze-your-content/\">focus keyword</a>. (New to keyword research? Check out this great <a href=\"https://www.blogtyrant.com/how-to-easily-find-the-best-keywords/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">beginner&#8217;s guide</a>.)</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Include your focus keyword in the slug, the title, and the meta description.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The AIOSEO plugin will give you other recommendations for using your focus keyphrase in your article.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-google-may-pull-a-different-meta-description\">Google May Pull a Different Meta Description</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>There&#8217;s no guarantee that Google (or other search engines) will display the meta description you wrote, but if it&#8217;s well-written, it&#8217;s likely it will appear. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>A good rule of thumb is, if Google can&#8217;t &#8220;write&#8221; a better one, yours will be picked to display.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That said, remember that you&#8217;re writing your meta description to focus on your focus keyword (search term). When people use a related but <em>different </em>search term, Google may pull an excerpt from your page that <em>better answers the searcher&#8217;s query.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s a good example. In the screenshot below, the meta description we wrote appears word-for-word in a search display for a given query.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"963\" height=\"384\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/24-meta-description-serp-example.png\" alt=\"meta description in serp example\" class=\"wp-image-177483\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/24-meta-description-serp-example.png 963w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/24-meta-description-serp-example-300x120.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/24-meta-description-serp-example-768x306.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/24-meta-description-serp-example-600x239.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/24-meta-description-serp-example-150x60.png 150w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/24-meta-description-serp-example-226x90.png 226w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But if we type in a different search term, Google pulls a different description, one that better matches the searcher&#8217;s question:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"270\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/25-meta-description-variation-1024x270.png\" alt=\"google serp creating meta description example\" class=\"wp-image-177484\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/25-meta-description-variation-1024x270.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/25-meta-description-variation-300x79.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/25-meta-description-variation-768x203.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/25-meta-description-variation-600x158.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/25-meta-description-variation-190x50.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/25-meta-description-variation-341x90.png 341w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/25-meta-description-variation.png 1107w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-be-careful-when-including-how-to-in-a-title\">Be Careful When Including &#8220;How to&#8221; in a Title</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When you search for &#8220;how to&#8221; content (like &#8220;how to fix drywall holes&#8221;), the dominant search results are <strong>step-by-step tutorials</strong>. This is what searchers <em>expect</em> when they see &#8220;how to&#8221; in a headline.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The &#8220;Diwali Special&#8221; example we cited earlier included &#8220;How to&#8221; in the headline:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"796\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/26-diwali-special-headline-example.png\" alt=\"how to article example\" class=\"wp-image-177485\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/26-diwali-special-headline-example.png 796w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/26-diwali-special-headline-example-300x117.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/26-diwali-special-headline-example-768x300.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/26-diwali-special-headline-example-600x234.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/26-diwali-special-headline-example-154x60.png 154w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/26-diwali-special-headline-example-230x90.png 230w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This interesting article doesn&#8217;t provide any recipes or step-by-step instructions, though. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In a case like this, it might be better to alter the headline or to add a recipe to the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-how-to-preview-rich-snippets\">How to Preview Rich Snippets</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have added schema markup to a web page, then you can preview the related rich snippet by following <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-run-a-rich-results-test-in-wordpress/\">these instructions</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Wondering what rich snippets (also called &#8220;rich results&#8221;) are? You can think of them as deluxe search engine displays. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Instead of the standard URL, title, and description, rich results include extras like star ratings, multiple images, prices, event dates, shipping information, or product stock status.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"457\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/product-rich-snippet-example-1024x457.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-178251\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/product-rich-snippet-example-1024x457.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/product-rich-snippet-example-300x134.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/product-rich-snippet-example-768x343.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/product-rich-snippet-example-600x268.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/product-rich-snippet-example-134x60.jpg 134w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/product-rich-snippet-example-202x90.jpg 202w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/product-rich-snippet-example.jpg 1206w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><em>These search results are examples of rich snippets. </em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Rich results are made possible with something called schema markup code. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can use AIOSEO to add schema markup to your pages with just a couple of button clicks. Find out how <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/setting-web-page-schema-markup-in-your-content/\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-dont-worry-about-measuring-snippets-by-pixels\">Don’t Worry About Measuring Snippets by Pixels</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Some Google SERP simulators caution that you should measure your snippet by pixels to determine if it would be cut off. We don’t believe that’s necessary. Here’s why.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While part of a page title may not fit in the SERP, Google’s algorithm prefers to not cut a word in two. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, it will cut a too-long title off <em>after a blank space,</em> preserving the prior word whole, if possible. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>We can see an example of this below, in the search engine result for a Danish article about the University of Copenhagen’s library.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"208\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/27-serp-snippet-truncated-example-1024x208.png\" alt=\"truncated title in serp\" class=\"wp-image-177486\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/27-serp-snippet-truncated-example-1024x208.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/27-serp-snippet-truncated-example-300x61.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/27-serp-snippet-truncated-example-768x156.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/27-serp-snippet-truncated-example-600x122.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/27-serp-snippet-truncated-example-190x39.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/27-serp-snippet-truncated-example-444x90.png 444w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/27-serp-snippet-truncated-example.png 1046w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>The word “videnskabeligt” is complete.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Google cut off the final word (<em>oplevelsesrum</em>).</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>We can see the missing word on the web page itself:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"442\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/28-universistetbibliotek-1024x442.jpg\" alt=\"screengrab of example web page\" class=\"wp-image-177487\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/28-universistetbibliotek-1024x442.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/28-universistetbibliotek-300x129.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/28-universistetbibliotek-768x331.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/28-universistetbibliotek-600x259.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/28-universistetbibliotek-139x60.jpg 139w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/28-universistetbibliotek-209x90.jpg 209w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/28-universistetbibliotek.jpg 1391w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Why pixels don’t matter</strong>: Where a title may be cut off depends on the length of words, number of words, and placement of spaces. (In this case, the title was cut off after 63 characters.)</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-is-a-google-serp-simulator-the-same-thing-as-a-serp-snippet-preview\">Is a Google SERP Simulator the same thing as a SERP Snippet Preview?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, these two things are fundamentally the same. Other terms used include SERP snippet generator and Google snippet preview. While search engines like Bing provide methods for previewing SERPs, all of the popular SERP snippet tools provide previews styled after Google’s search engine results pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-bonus-tips-to-boost-your-on-page-seo\">Bonus Tips</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are two easy action steps you can take to improve your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/adding-breadcrumbs-to-your-site-using-the-aioseo-breadcrumbs-block/\">Add breadcrumbs</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress/\">Add a table of contents</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Feeling adventurous? <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo-and-get-more-traffic/\">Add some FAQs</a> to your site to boost SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And don&#8217;t forget to plan for <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/lead-generation/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">capturing leads</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-keep-moving-forward\">Keep Moving Forward</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article has helped you learn an easy way to use a SERP snippet preview tool. We recommend exploring proven ways to get <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ways-to-increase-your-organic-clickthrough-rates/\">more traffic</a>. Plus, learn how to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/small-business-seo-scams-how-to-detect-and-avoid-them/\" title=\"\">avoid SEO scams</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-serp-snippet-tool/\">How to Use a SERP Snippet Tool to Improve Your Click-Through Rates</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-serp-snippet-tool/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"How to Use SEO Data to Boost Your Search Rankings \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:152:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-seo-data-to-boost-search-rankings/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-use-seo-data-to-boost-search-rankings\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-seo-data-to-boost-search-rankings/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 10 Apr 2023 15:40:38 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"Google Search Console integration\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"search statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"seo data\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=162863\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:419:\"<p>Would you like to know how to use SEO data to boost your search rankings? Data plays a huge role in helping you design and deploy impactful SEO campaigns. That’s why you need to know the right SEO data to&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-seo-data-to-boost-search-rankings/\">How to Use SEO Data to Boost Your Search Rankings </a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23900:\"<p>Would you like to know how to use SEO data to boost your search rankings?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Data plays a huge role in helping you design and deploy impactful SEO campaigns. That’s why you need to know the right SEO data to collect and how to use it to boost your rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we’ll show you which SEO data you need, how to interpret it, and how to use it to enhance your SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-is-seo-data-and-why-is-it-important\">What is SEO Data, and Why is it Important?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-7-ways-to-use-seo-data-to-boost-your-rankings\">7 Ways to Use SEO Data to Boost Your Rankings</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-1-check-for-and-optimize-keywords-that-are-dropping-in-rankings\">1. Check for and Optimize Keywords that are Dropping in Rankings</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-2-create-a-strategy-to-help-you-move-up-in-rankings\">2. Create a Strategy to Help You Move Up in Rankings</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-3-find-internal-linking-opportunities\">3. Find Internal Linking Opportunities</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-4-monitor-impressions-to-understand-and-boost-your-reach\">4. Monitor Impressions to Understand and Boost Your Reach</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-5-increase-average-ctr-to-boost-your-rankings\">5. Increase Average CTR to Boost Your Rankings</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-6-set-effective-s-m-a-r-t-seo-goals\">6. Set Effective S.M.A.R.T. SEO Goals</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-7-keep-tabs-on-page-speed\">7. Keep Tabs on Page Speed</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-seo-data-its-the-edge-you-need-to-outrank-your-competitors\">SEO Data: It’s the Edge You Need to Outrank Your Competitors</a></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-what-is-seo-data-and-why-is-it-important\">What is SEO Data, and Why is it Important?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>SEO data refers to any metrics used to create and monitor SEO campaigns. Some examples of SEO data include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Organic traffic</strong>: Organic traffic refers to visitors who visit your website from search engine results instead of paid ads. The more organic traffic you drive, the stronger the indication that your SEO strategy is working.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Search impressions</strong>: Search impressions refer to the instances your content appears on the user&#8217;s screen. More impressions indicate that your organic reach is increasing.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Organic rankings/Average position</strong>: This metric shows your position on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-are-serps/\" title=\"What Are SERPs (And Why Are they Important to SEO)?\">search engine results pages</a> (SERPs) in relation to competing content. This doesn’t factor in ads.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Average clickthrough rate (CTR)</strong>: This shows the average number of times searchers click on your search listing in proportion to impressions.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Page speed</strong>: Measured in milliseconds, page speed refers to the time it takes for a web page to load. This is an important metric as it impacts your <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-optimize-core-web-vitals-for-wordpress-ultimate-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">Core Web Vitals</a>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>And more</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>These metrics, and more, are essential to helping you measure the performance of your SEO strategy. They’re also vital in helping you create better iterations of your campaigns.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-7-ways-to-use-seo-data-to-boost-your-rankings\">7 Ways to Use SEO Data to Boost Your Rankings</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to use SEO Data to boost your search rankings?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some tips to help you do that.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-1-check-for-and-optimize-keywords-that-are-dropping-in-rankings\">1. Check for and Optimize Keywords that are Dropping in Rankings</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the first ways to use SEO data to boost your rankings is to check keyword performance. This is easy to do in WordPress if you are an <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">All In One SEO</a> (AIOSEO) user. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is a powerful SEO tool with powerful SEO data reporting functionality.\" class=\"wp-image-170372\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/aioseo-600x267.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/aioseo-135x60.png 135w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/aioseo-203x90.png 203w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">AIOSEO</a> is the best WordPress SEO plugin on the market and has been downloaded over 100 million times. Millions of savvy website owners and marketers trust the plugin to help them dominate SERPs and drive relevant site traffic. This is because the plugin has many <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/\" title=\"Features\">powerful SEO features and modules</a> to help you optimize your website for search engines and users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For step-by-step instructions on how to install AIOSEO, check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"Installing All in One SEO Pro\">installation guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the most beloved features in AIOSEO is the brand-new <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/google-search-console-integration/\" title=\"Announcing AIOSEO 4.3.0 – Get Powerful Insights With Our Google Search Console Integration\">Search Statistics module</a>, our Google Search Console integration.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To monitor your keywords, simply go to <strong>Search Statistics » Keyword Rankings</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"288\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/search-statistics-keyword-rankings.png\" alt=\"You can monitor keyword performance using Search Statistics.\" class=\"wp-image-177217\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/search-statistics-keyword-rankings.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/search-statistics-keyword-rankings-300x123.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/search-statistics-keyword-rankings-600x246.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/search-statistics-keyword-rankings-146x60.png 146w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/search-statistics-keyword-rankings-219x90.png 219w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Keyword Performance report will show you all your keywords, those that are dropping in rankings and those that are going up.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"401\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-track-seo-keyword-rankings-top-losing.png\" alt=\"Search Statistics gives you valuable SEO data such as Top Winning and Top Losing keywords.\" class=\"wp-image-177220\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-track-seo-keyword-rankings-top-losing.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-track-seo-keyword-rankings-top-losing-300x171.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-track-seo-keyword-rankings-top-losing-600x343.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-track-seo-keyword-rankings-top-losing-105x60.png 105w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-track-seo-keyword-rankings-top-losing-158x90.png 158w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To boost your rankings and drive more traffic to your site, you’ll want to note the keywords that are dropping in rankings. Once you’ve compiled your list, revisit your content to better optimize for those keywords.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-2-create-a-strategy-to-help-you-move-up-in-rankings\">2. Create a Strategy to Help You Move Up in Rankings</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another way to use SEO data to boost your rankings is to monitor your position on search engine results pages (SERPs).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can easily do this with AIOSEO’s Search Statistics module, as it lets you easily track your content and keyword positions right from your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"373\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-position.png\" alt=\"You can easily track your keyword positions using AIOSEO.\" class=\"wp-image-177221\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-position.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-position-300x160.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-position-600x320.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-position-113x60.png 113w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-position-169x90.png 169w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Knowing where your content ranks is vital as it helps you know how to get it to move up in rankings. And in case you didn’t know, research shows that moving up one position in rankings can result in as much as a <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/google-ctr-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">2.8% increase in clickthrough rates</a> (CTR).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For detailed tips on how to move your content up in rankings, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/search-statistics-power-hacks-to-help-boost-your-rankings/\" title=\"6 Search Statistics Power Hacks to Help Boost Your Rankings\">check out this guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-3-find-internal-linking-opportunities\">3. Find Internal Linking Opportunities</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Internal linking is another critical ingredient in boosting rankings. This is why checking for internal linking opportunities should be part of your SEO data collecting and monitoring. Doing this is easy, thanks to AIOSEO’s <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/internal-link-assistant/\" title=\"Link Assistant\">Link Assistant</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"329\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/elementor-seo-internal-linking-with-link-assistant-getting-started.png\" alt=\"Link Assistant is a powerful tool you can use to boost your internal linking strategy.\" class=\"wp-image-81561\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/elementor-seo-internal-linking-with-link-assistant-getting-started.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/elementor-seo-internal-linking-with-link-assistant-getting-started-300x141.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/elementor-seo-internal-linking-with-link-assistant-getting-started-600x282.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Link Assistant is a powerful module that crawls your site and checks for internal and external links and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-easily-find-and-fix-orphan-pages-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Easily Find and Fix Orphan Pages in WordPress\">orphaned posts</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"381\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/internal-linking-with-link-assistant-links-report.png\" alt=\"To help boost your internal linking strategy, Link Assistant\" class=\"wp-image-79017\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/internal-linking-with-link-assistant-links-report.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/internal-linking-with-link-assistant-links-report-300x163.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/internal-linking-with-link-assistant-links-report-600x327.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The best part about the tool is that it checks linking opportunities and automates internal link building between your posts. As a result, you can build links faster and more efficiently.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the biggest advantages of building internal links is that it makes it easier for search engines to crawl and index your content. In addition, strategic internal linking also helps you build topical authority. These 2 benefits, and more, play a huge role in boosting your rankings.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-link-assistant-to-optimize-your-internal-linking-strategy/\" title=\"How to Use Link Assistant to Optimize Your Internal Linking Strategy\">Check out this tutorial</a> for more information on using Link Assistant to speed up your internal linking and boost on-page SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-4-monitor-impressions-to-understand-and-boost-your-reach\">4. Monitor Impressions to Understand and Boost Your Reach</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Impressions refer to the number of times searchers have seen your search listing on SERPs. This metric is not action-based but helps show your content’s reach.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"369\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-impressions.png\" alt=\"Search Impressions are another valuable piece of SEO data you can use to boost your search rankings.\" class=\"wp-image-177223\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-impressions.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-impressions-300x158.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-impressions-600x315.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-impressions-114x60.png 114w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-impressions-171x90.png 171w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Impressions are important to your SEO as they are a general indicator of how well your SEO strategy is performing. More impressions signify that people are seeing your content. They also increase the chances of people clicking on your link.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the most effective ways to increase your impressions is to target the right keywords and optimize for them. You also need to ensure your content meets search intent. Another way is to build internal links strategically, as this helps increase your topical authority. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-5-increase-average-ctr-to-boost-your-rankings\">5. Increase Average CTR to Boost Your Rankings</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Average CTR (Avg. CTR) is the number of clicks your search listing receives divided by impressions. This is another vital piece of SEO data you can use to boost your rankings. If you are an AIOSEO user, you don’t have to switch to Google Search Console or any other tool to get this metric. Instead, you can find it in the Search Statistics module in the Keyword Performance report. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"354\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-average-ctr.png\" alt=\"Knowing your average CTR will help you create strategies to boost organic clicks.\" class=\"wp-image-177224\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-average-ctr.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-average-ctr-300x151.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-average-ctr-600x303.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-average-ctr-119x60.png 119w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/how-to-use-seo-data-average-ctr-178x90.png 178w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Improving your CTR is a fantastic way to boost rankings, as it signals to search engines that users find your content valuable. One way you can improve your CTR is by <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-faq-schema-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Add FAQ Schema in WordPress [The Easiest Way]\">adding FAQ schema</a> to your content. Doing so optimizes your search snippets for visibility and leads to rich snippets that offer users a better experience.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"337\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-faqs.png\" alt=\"Adding FAQ schema to your content helps boost your online visibility.\" class=\"wp-image-159662\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-faqs.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-faqs-300x144.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-faqs-600x288.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-faqs-125x60.png 125w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-faqs-187x90.png 187w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Other ways to increase your average CTR include optimizing your URL, title, and meta description.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For other tips on boosting your organic CTR, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ways-to-increase-your-organic-clickthrough-rates/\" title=\"8 Proven Ways to Increase Your Organic Clickthrough Rates\">check out this article</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-6-set-effective-s-m-a-r-t-seo-goals\">6. Set Effective S.M.A.R.T. SEO Goals</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Data plays a huge role in helping you set effective goals for your SEO campaigns. That’s why you should set <a href=\"https://www.searchenginejournal.com/smart-seo-goals/448096/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">S.M.A.R.T. SEO goals</a> using the data you collect from your site. For example, we created the Search Statistics module to help you track content performance and keyword rankings. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"390\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-content-performance.png\" alt=\"You can track content performance using AIOSEO\'s Search Statistics module.\" class=\"wp-image-159654\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-content-performance.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-content-performance-300x167.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-content-performance-600x333.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-content-performance-108x60.png 108w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-content-performance-162x90.png 162w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This is essential SEO data you can use to set simple SEO goals. For example, getting 1-3 articles in the top 10 positions in X months. Or you can set a goal of maintaining 5 articles in the top 20.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also use this SEO data to set content goals. One way to do this is to check your content and keywords that are performing well. This will give you an idea of the content your audience is hungry for. As a result, you can set goals to replicate similar content and have it rank as well as your top-performing content.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-7-keep-tabs-on-page-speed\">7. Keep Tabs on Page Speed</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Page loading speed is an essential ranking factor. That’s why your SEO data must include page speed reports. You can get this in Search Statistics by going to <strong>Search Statistics » SEO Statistics</strong>. Next, scroll down to the <strong>Content Performance</strong> section.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"404\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/best-content-optimization-tools-aioseo-search-statistics.png\" alt=\"Check your content performance report to get the page speed of each of your web pages.\" class=\"wp-image-177231\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/best-content-optimization-tools-aioseo-search-statistics.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/best-content-optimization-tools-aioseo-search-statistics-300x173.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/best-content-optimization-tools-aioseo-search-statistics-600x345.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/best-content-optimization-tools-aioseo-search-statistics-104x60.png 104w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/best-content-optimization-tools-aioseo-search-statistics-156x90.png 156w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In this section, you can click the link to the page you want to test for speed. This will generate a report that includes a Speed Test.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"325\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/seo-reporting-speed-test.png\" alt=\"Improving page speed is a vital component of boosting your rankings.\" class=\"wp-image-159681\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/seo-reporting-speed-test.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/seo-reporting-speed-test-300x139.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/seo-reporting-speed-test-600x278.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/seo-reporting-speed-test-130x60.png 130w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/seo-reporting-speed-test-194x90.png 194w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p>If your speed test results are poor, you can work on improving your score. This can have a positive impact on rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For detailed instructions on improving your page load speed, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/10-quick-easy-ways-to-speed-up-your-site/\" title=\"10 Ways to Speed up Your WordPress Site\">check out this informative guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-seo-data-its-the-edge-you-need-to-outrank-your-competitors\">SEO Data: It’s the Edge You Need to Outrank Your Competitors</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Leveraging SEO data is an excellent way to get ahead of the competition on SERPs. It has many advantages, including helping you monitor your performance and create better iterations of your SEO strategy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Most of all, the right SEO data can help you boost your rankings on SERPs, resulting in more traffic, engagement, and sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this post helped you find the best content optimization tool for SEO for your site. You may also want to check out other articles on our blog, like our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-ai-seo-software-to-boost-rankings/\" title=\"How to Use AI SEO Software to Boost Your Rankings\">using AI software to boost rankings</a> or our tutorial on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-product-review-schema-in-wordpress/\">adding product review schema in WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.  </p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-seo-data-to-boost-search-rankings/\">How to Use SEO Data to Boost Your Search Rankings </a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://aioseo.com/ho